import{_ as t,c as a,b as i,o}from"./chunks/framework.Bh4f_7Kc.js";const c=JSON.parse('{"title":"","description":"","frontmatter":{},"headers":[],"relativePath":"guide/William James.md","filePath":"guide/William James.md"}'),n={name:"guide/William James.md"};function p(s,e,r,h,l,u){return o(),a("div",null,e[0]||(e[0]=[i("<p>If you can change your mind, you can change your life.</p><p>Change your thoughts and you can change your life.</p><p>---002---</p><p>Sow an action, reap a habit; sow a habit, reap a character; sow a character, reap a destiny.</p><p>---003---</p><p>Our weaknesses may provide us with an unexpected strength.</p><p>---004---</p><p>The art of being wise is knowing what to overlook.</p><p>The way to become wise is to know what to ignore.</p><p>---005---</p><p>The most pressing need in human nature is the desire to be affirmed.</p><p>---006---</p><p>No matter how many good advices you know, no matter how good your conditions are, if you don&#39;t use them concretely when opportunities come, you won&#39;t make progress. If you have good ideas but don&#39;t contribute them, your life won&#39;t improve.</p><p>---007---</p><p>The deepest principle in human nature is the craving to be appreciated.</p><p>The deepest instinct in human nature is the desire to be appreciated.</p><p>---008---</p><p>Man&#39;s problem is not what he wants to do, but what he wants to be.</p><p>---009---</p><p>The lies you tell life, life will tell you back. There is no chance of luck.</p><p>---010---</p><p>People can change their lives by changing their attitudes.</p><p>---011---</p><p>Take action first, pretend to be happy, and your heart will be happy.</p><p>---012---</p><p>The greatest discovery of my generation is that a human being can alter his life by altering his attitudes.</p><p>The greatest discovery of my generation is that humans can change their lives by changing their attitudes.</p><p>---013---</p><p>Sow an action, you will reap a habit; sow a habit, you will reap a character; sow a character, you will reap a destiny. Good behavior habits are not innate, but can be cultivated. Habit is such a tenacious force! It can dominate a person&#39;s life. Therefore, we should establish a good habit from an early age, through education and cultivation, until we benefit from it for life.</p><p>---014---</p><p>The help of a small person is always a great help, and the greatest factor is precisely because of his smallness.</p><p>---015---</p><p>Each of us feels, deep down, that a carefree and indifferent attitude toward life will compensate for all his shortcomings.</p><p>---016---</p><p>When people grow up, they often struggle to make a living. The routines in life become more and more numerous, and the years become empty. The enthusiasm they had when they first knew the world no longer exists.</p><p>---017---</p><p>True culture lives on sympathy and admiration, not on hatred and contempt.</p><p>---018---</p><p>If it were possible, the cruelest punishment for a man would be to give him freedom, to let him wander about in society, but to ignore him and not pay any attention to him. When he appears, no one would even turn aside to show him a sign; when he speaks, no one would respond or pay any attention to his behavior. If everyone around us ignores us and simply ignores our existence, it won&#39;t be long before we are filled with anger and feel a strong and inexplicable despair. Compared to this torture, cruel corporal punishment will become a relief.</p><p>---019---</p><p>The depths of the great mass,human nature is the desire to be appreciated.</p><p>The deepest quality in human nature is the desire to be appreciated.</p><p>-----William James</p><p>---020---</p><p>The art of being wise is knowing what to ignore.</p><p>---021---</p><p>Human thought is the cause of all things. If you sow an idea, you will reap an action; if you sow an action, you will reap a habit; if you sow a habit, you will reap a character; if you sow a character, you will reap a destiny.</p><p>---022---</p><p>Philosophy lives in words, and truth and facts flow into our lives in ways far superior to linguistic formulas.</p><p>---023---</p><p>The art of wisdom is the art of knowing what to tolerate</p><p>---024---</p><p>Generosity is the greatest of all things.</p><p>---025---</p><p>The moment a person stops growing, no matter how old he is, is the moment he begins to decline.</p><p>---026---</p><p>Evil cannot prevail over good, and good cannot prevail over madness</p><p>---027---</p><p>All human endeavors can be traced back to the creation of inventors, great and small, and the imitation of the rest. Individuals point the way and set the pattern. The competition between patterns is the history of the world.</p><p>---028---</p><p>The first principle of human nature is the desire to be admired</p><p>---029---</p><p>In most cases, if we remembered everything, we would be as unlucky as if we remembered nothing.</p><p>---030---</p><p>Religion is a very important chapter in the history of human egoism.</p><p>---031---</p><p>Many people think they are thinking, but in reality they are just rearranging their biases.</p><p>---032---</p><p>Once the crystal snowflake falls into warm hands, it is no longer a crystal snowflake.</p><p>---033---</p><p>The art of wisdom is the art of choosing and giving up.</p><p>---034---</p><p>The greatest desire in human nature is to be recognized and praised by others.</p><p>---035---</p><p>The highest good is to achieve the greatest need at the lowest cost (sacrifice).</p><p>---036---</p><p>The strongest desire in human nature is to be recognized by others.</p><p>---037---</p><p>The deep nature of human nature</p><p>It is the desire to be appreciated</p><p>---038---</p><p>Sobriety always means retreat, discrimination and opposition; drunkenness always means expansion, agreement and approval.</p><p>---039---</p><p>Faith is life</p><p>---040---</p><p>Many people think they are thinking, but in fact, they are just reorganizing their prejudices.</p><p>---041---</p><p>Everyone knows that running away increases fear, and that symptoms of sadness and anger are self-reinforcing, with each cry making the sadness more intense, which in turn makes us cry more, until we are exhausted. When we are angry, our emotional expressions make us angrier.</p><p>---042---</p><p>Deep in the root of human nature, there is a strong desire for the appreciation of others.</p><p>---043---</p><p>The madman&#39;s terrifying hallucinations are all drawn from people&#39;s daily lives.</p><p>---044---</p><p>There is only one you in the world, and this expression is unique. If you block it, it will not exist through other media and will be lost forever.</p><p>---045---</p><p>Everyone&#39;s life has a definite form, but it is actually made up of various habits.</p><p>---046---</p><p>Acceptance of what has happened is the first step in overcoming consequences of any misfortune.</p><p>---047---</p><p>The body is the mind, the mind is the body.</p><p>---048---</p><p>Accept all unexpected events as they are, and then the first step is to overcome the unfortunate consequences.</p><p>---049---</p><ol><li><p>Generosity is the greatest of all things.</p></li><li><p>The art of wisdom is the art of knowing what to tolerate</p></li></ol><p>---050---</p><p>The greatest discovery of our generation is that human beings can change their destiny by changing their attitudes.</p><p>---051---</p><p>Classic Quotes</p><ol><li><p>Generosity is the greatest of all things.</p></li><li><p>The art of wisdom is the art of knowing what to tolerate.</p></li><li><p>Religion is an extremely important chapter in the history of human egoism.</p></li><li><p>The rescue of a small person is always a great rescue, and the greatest factor is precisely because of his insignificance.</p></li><li><p>Make yourself feel brave, act brave, and use willpower to achieve this goal. Courage is</p></li></ol><p>It can replace fear.</p><p>---052---</p><p>The deepest principle of human nature is the desire for respect.</p><p>---053---</p><p>The feeling of powerlessness is caused by the patient&#39;s internal countercurrent that prevents him from giving his all. It&#39;s like he is driving a car with his foot on the brake. The car will inevitably slow down, and he could have done everything much faster. It&#39;s not that he is not working hard enough, on the contrary, he has to put a lot of energy into everything he does.</p>",114)]))}const m=t(n,[["render",p]]);export{c as __pageData,m as default};
